    "Furthermore, the system's response time grew longer and occasionally failed to respond as the number of photographs increased which was more common in previous versions.",
    "Moreover, when GPT-4 processed up to 10 images simultaneously, there was a noticeable decline in classification accuracy compared to processing images individually.",
    "Additionally, continuous image processing might introduce more noise or variability into the data, heightening the risk of system overload.",
    "This can lead to decreased responsiveness or even system crashes.",
